      xxix)     CIVPERS: decrease in civilian personnel and funding resulting from the transfer of mission from Commander, U.S.     -5,413
        Pacific Fleet, Combat Support Forces, to Commander, U.S. Fleet Forces Command (USFF) as part of the disestablishment
        of NECC Pacific headquarters and realignment of duties to NECC USFF. (Baseline: $487,048; -41 civilian FTE)
      xxx) Decrease resulting from Navy Expeditionary Combat Command transfer from Commander, U.S. Pacific Fleet, Combat            -6,403
        Support Forces, to Commander, U.S. Fleet Forces Command (USFF) represents the disestablishment of NECC Pacific
        headquarters and realignment of duties to NECC USFF. (Baseline: $519,505)
      xxxi)     Navy Expeditionary Combat Enterprise: decrease to the Navy Fleet Liaison Unit and the Navy accepting risk to        -6,968
        support maintenance and sustainment of Joint EOD Publications, Information Systems, and EOD tools and equipment.
        (Baseline:
        $228,183)                                                                                                                   -7,007
      xxxii) Naval Information Forces (NAVIFOR): decrease in development and integration of Information Warfare (IW)
        informed Live Virtual Constructive (LVC)-enabled training events for Fleet Response Training Plan (FRTP) resources
        realigned to fund higher department priorities. (Baseline: $39,768)                                                         -8,044
      xxxiii) Naval Facilities Expeditionary Programs: decrease to Phased Replacement/Tech Refresh (PR/TR) base efforts which
        includes PR/TR of non-major end items in the expeditionary table of allowance (TOA) for the following Expeditionary
        programs: Construction Equipment (CE), Expeditionary Basing (EB), Industrial Production and Handling (IPH), Mobile
        Mission Support (MMS), Personal Gear Infantry (PGI), and Tactical Vehicle (TV). (Baseline: $38,308)                         -8,664
      xxxiv) Naval Forces Central Command (NAVCENT): decrease in combat support forces for ISA airbase operations, Task
        Force 59 Unmanned systems and Counter Unmanned Aerial Systems (CUSA) support for Naval Forces Central Command.
        (Baseline: $78,922)                                                                                                        -11,717
      xxxv) Diving and Salvage: reduction in supplies and materials, transportation by Air Mobility Command (AMC), depot
        maintenance, and purchased communications supporting Mobile Diving and Salvage Units. (Baseline: $44,499)                  -23,966
      xxxvi) Navy Expeditionary Combat Enterprise: decrease driven by the Naval Expeditionary Combat Enterprise (NECE) to
        realign funding to support NECE Cost Capability Model (NCCM) based requirements to meet up to 90% fleet requirement
        priorities. (Baseline: $228,183)                                                                                           -24,073
      xxxvii) Navy Expeditionary Combat Command: decrease in equipment maintenance by contract, facility sustainment,
        restoration, and modernization, and IT contract services supporting Naval Construction Force, and Maritime Expeditionary
        Security Force (MESF). (Baseline: $519,505)                                                                                -29,072
      xxxviii) Efficiency – Workforce Optimization: Reduces civilian personnel full-time equivalents and funding to optimize the
        workforce in compliance with Executive Order 14210, Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency
        Workforce Optimization Initiative.                                                                                         -53,244
        (Baseline: $487,048; -124 civilian FTE)
      xxxix) Efficiency – Contract Services: Reduces contracts for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and
        advance the policies of the Administration in alignment with Executive Order 14222, Implementing the President's
        Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative. (Baseline: $2,359,834)
